  <div class="content">
    <h1>How to Apply</h1>
    <hr>
    <p>Enrollment for the Ultrasound Training Program is conducted through our online learning portal.

    After submitting the application and completing enrolment, final acceptance is subject to approval by the Academy. Upon acceptance, students will be formally registered and granted access to the course platform.

    The program is delivered in a module-based structure. Once enrolled, students are assigned to each module sequentially. Teaching is conducted through virtual classroom lectures, supported by coursework and continuous assessments. Progression to the next module is permitted only after successful completion of the current module and its assessments.

    After completing all academic modules, eligible students will be transitioned to the hands-on practical training phase, followed by placement exposure where applicable. Throughout the practical phase, students are required to maintain a log book documenting clinical learning and competencies.

    Upon successful completion of all modules, assessments, hands-on training, and log book requirements, students will be awarded course completion and graduation status, subject to Academy policies.</p>
  </div>

